rime Thriller Awards\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[Room at the Top (2012 film)|''Room at the Top'']]\n|Broadcasting Press Guild Award\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" |2014\n|''Keeping Rosy''\n|Fantasporto Awards\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[The Village (2013 TV series)|''The Village'']]\n|BAFTA TV Award\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|Broadcasting Press Guild Awards\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2018\n|''Three Girls'' \n|Broadcasting Press Guild Awards\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|\n|UK Theatre Award\n|Outstanding contribution to British Theatre\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|''Funny Cow''\n|British Independent Film Awards\n|Best Actress\n| {{pending}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/4ce2bb4f41673 Maxine Peake] at the [[British Film Institute]]\n* {{IMDb name|0668845}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Peake, Maxine}}\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actors at the Royal Exchange, Manchester]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Royal Academy of Dramatic Art]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Salford]]\n[[Category:English feminists]]\n[[Category:English film actresses]]\n[[Category:English radio actresses]]\n[[Category:English Shakespearean actresses]]\n[[Category:English socialists]]\n[[Category:English stage actresses]]\n[[Category:English television actresses]]\n[[Category:Labour Party (UK) people]]\n[[Category:People educated at Canon Slade School]]\n[[Category:People from Westhoughton]]\n[[Category:Socialist feminists]]\n[[Category:Communist Party of Britain members]]\n[[Category:Best Actress BAFTA Award (television) nominees]]\n", "name_user": "Viennese Waltz", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTelevision:lc", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maxine_Peake"}
{"title_page": "Traveler (South Korean TV series)", "text_new": "{{short description|Korean television program}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Traveler [[File:Republic Of Korea Broadcasting-TV Rating System(15).svg|24px|Republic_Of_Korea_Broadcasting-TV_Rating_System(15).svg]]\n| image                    = Traveller_(South_Korean_TV_series)_poster.jpg\n| image_size               = 250px\n| caption                  = Season 2 promotional poster\n| native_name              = {{Infobox name module|hangul=\ud2b8\ub798\ube14\ub7ec}}\n| genre                    = [[Reality television]] <br> [[Travel documentary]]\n| starring                 = [[#Cast|Various actors]]\n| country                  = [[South Korea]]\n| language                 = [[Korean language|Korean]]\n| num_seasons              = 2\n| num_episodes             = 17 (as of {{date|3/28/2020}})\n| list_episodes            = #Episodes\n| location                 = [[South Korea]], [[Cuba]], [[Argentina]]\n| camera                   = [[Multiple-camera setup|Multi-camera]]\n| runtime                  = 67\u201380 minutes\n| company                  = [[JTBC]]\n| channel                  = JTBC\n| first_aired              = {{start date|2019|2|21|df=y}}\t\n| last_aired               = {{end date|present}}\n| website                  = http://tv.jtbc.joins.com/travelerargentina\n}}\n{{Infobox Korean name\n|title = [[Korean name]]\n|hangul = \ud2b8\ub798\ube14\ub7ec\n|rr = teulaebeulleo\n|mr= T'\u016draeb\u016dll\u014f\n|color = lavender\n}}\n'''''Traveler''''' ({{ko-hhrm|\ud2b8\ub798\ube14\ub7ec||Teulaebeulleo}}) is a South Korean [[Television comedy|television entertainment program]] which airs on [[JTBC]]. It is about actors going on a [[Backpacking (travel)|backpacking trip]].<ref>{{cite web|first=Ah-young|last=Kang|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/nation/2019/02/688_264321.html|title='Traveler' captures glimpse of backpacking|date=24 February 2019|website=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=1 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301102558/https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/nation/2019/02/688_264321.html|archivedate=1 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe first season features [[Lee Je-hoon]] and [[Ryu Jun-yeol]] as they travel to [[Cuba]]. It aired on Thursdays from 21 February 2019 to 25 April 2019.<ref name=sea1>{{citeweb|url=http://sports.donga.com/3/all/20181218/93351353/1|title=\u2018\ud2b8\ub798\ube14\ub7ec\u2019 \uce21 \u201c\uc774\uc81c\ud6c8 \ucd9c\uc5f0 \ud655\uc815, 2019\ub144 \uc0c1\ubc18\uae30 \ubc29\uc1a1\u201d [\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5]|date=18 December 2018|website=Sports Donga|lang=ko|accessdate=24 February 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190103161224/http://sports.donga.com/3/all/20181218/93351353/1|archivedate=3 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe second season features [[Ahn Jae-hong (actor)|Ahn Jae-hong]], [[Kang Ha-neul]] and [[Ong Seong-wu]] as they travel to [[Argentina]]. It is broadcast on Saturdays starting from 15 February 2020.<ref name=sea2>{{citeweb|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1111265458|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] '\ud2b8\ub798\ube14\ub7ec' \uac15\ud558\ub298X\uc548\uc7ac\ud64dX\uc639\uc131\uc6b0, 29\uc77c \uc544\ub974\ud5e8\ud2f0\ub098 \ub3d9\ubc18 \ucd9c\uad6d|website=Osen|lang=ko|date=22 November 2019|accessdate=22 November 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122063527/http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1111265458|archivedate=22 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\n===Season 1===\nThe program is about two travelers, who went to [[Cuba]], that combines trips and documentaries whom take a [[Backpacking (travel)|backpacking]] trip and enjoy a variety of experiences in the local area. For two weeks ('''26 December 2018 \u2013 10 January 2019'''), both travelers backpacked in Cuba to learn about Che Guevara's freedom and revolution, [[Buena Vista Social Club]]'s brilliant melodies and enjoy the refreshing feeling of old cars (1950's to 1970's) and [[mojito]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://tv.jtbc.joins.com/plan/pr10011013|title=Program Information (Season 1)|lang=ko|website=JTBC|accessdate=24 February 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190224173526/http://tv.jtbc.joins.com/plan/pr10011013|archivedate=24 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> This backpacking trip is without the interference of the production crews and both travelers have to make decisions of their choice together on finding private accommodations, known as [[Casa particular|casa]], eating and transportation.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.osen.co.kr/article/G1111085601|title=[\uc0ac\uc9c4]\ud2b8\ub798\ube14\ub7ec \ub958\uc900\uc5f4-\uc774\uc81c\ud6c8,'\ucfe0\ubc14\ub85c \ud568\uaed8 \ub5a0\ub098\uc694'|website=Osen|lang=ko|date=21 February 2019|accessdate=24 February 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190719101414/http://www.osen.co.kr/article/G1111085601|archivedate=19 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n[[File:Cuba, Havana, cars in 2014.jpg|thumb|center|400px|Vintage cars of 1950's \u2013 1970s in Havana]]\n\n===Season 2===\nNew travelers Ahn Jae-hong, Kang Ha-neul and Ong Seong-wu visit Argentina. They became real travelers in the original landscape of Argentina and enjoyed the beauty of a dozen times more colorful than their changing attire. They will go to places like [[Iguazu Falls]],  [[Perito Moreno Glacier]] and fighting against the wind on the road across [[Patagonia]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://tv.jtbc.joins.com/plan/pr10011156|title=Program Information (Season 2)|website=JTBC|lang=ko|date=6 February 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206121706/http://tv.jtbc.joins.com/plan/pr10011156|archivedate=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Airtime==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+\n!width=50|Season\n!width=300|Air date\n!width=300|Airtime\n|-\n| 1 || 21 February \u2013 25 April 2019 || Thursdays at 11:00 PM [[Time in South Korea|KST]]\n|-\n| 2 || 15 February 2020 \u2013 present || Saturdays at 7:40 PM KST\n|-\n|}\n\n==Cast==\n===Season 1===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+\n!style=width:175px| Name\n!style=width:100px| Episode\n!Ref.\n|-\n|[[Ryu Jun-yeol]]\n|1 \u2013 10\n|rowspan=2|<ref name=sea1/>\n|-\n|[[Lee Je-hoon]]\n|3 \u2013 10\n|-\n|}\n\n===Season 2===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+\n!style=width:175px| Name\n!style=width:100px| Episode\n!Ref.\n|-\n|[[Ahn Jae-hong (actor)|Ahn Jae-hong]]\n|rowspan=3|1 \u2013 present\n|rowspan=3|<ref name=sea2/>\n|-\n|[[Kang Ha-neul]]\n|-\n|[[Ong Seong-wu]]\n|-\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n==Episodes==\n===Season 1 (2019)===\n{{hidden begin\n|title=List of episodes in Season 1\n|titlestyle=background:PaleTurquoise;\n}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+\n!width=\"30\" |{{abbr|Ep.|Episode}}\n!width=\"150\" |Broadcast date\n!width=\"60\" |Day\n!Filming date\n!Location\n!Notes\n|-\n!1\n|21 February 2019\n|1 \u2013 3\n|{{small|26\u201328 December 2018}}\n|rowspan=2 style=background:#7DF9FF|[[Havana]]\n|rowspan=2 style=text-align:left|\n*Je-hoon was not available for Day 1 to 6 due to filming schedule conflict with 2018 SBS Drama Awards.\n*Jun-yeol arrived at Havana late evening of Day 1 and checked-in to his casa.\n*Jun-yeol travelled and phototaking within Havana in Day 2 & 3.\n|-\n!rowspan=2|2\n|rowspan=2|28 February 2019\n|rowspan=2|4 \u2013 5\n|rowspan=2|{{small|29\u201330 December 2018}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2 style=background:PaleGreen|[[Vi\u00f1ales]]\n|\n*Jun-yeol did not go to Vi\u00f1ales in the afternoon of Day 4 as his private car did not arrive. He managed to get another car and arrived at Vi\u00f1ales in the evening.\n|-\n!rowspan=2|3\n|rowspan=2|7 March 2019\n|6\n|{{small|31 December 2018}}\n|\n*Jun-yeol celebrated New Year's Day in Vi\u00f1ales.\n|-\n|7\n|{{small|1 January 2019}}\n|rowspan=3 style=background:#7DF9FF|Havana\n|\n*Jun-yeol returned to Havana to meet Je-hoon who finally arrived in Cuba.\n|-\n!rowspan=2|4\n|rowspan=2|14 March 2019\n|8\n|{{small|2 January 2019}}\n|\n*Je-hoon toured around Havana with Jun-yeol as the tour guide on Day 8 & 9.\n|-\n|rowspan=2|9\n|rowspan=2|{{small|3 January 2019}}\n|\u2014\n|-\n!5\n|21 March 2019\n|rowspan=3 style=background:mistyrose|[[Playa Gir\u00f3n]]\n|\n*Jun-yeol and Je-hoon set off to Playa Gir\u00f3n on the second half of the Day 9 and arrived in the evening.\n|-\n!6\n|28 March 2019\n|10\n|{{small|4 January 2019}}\n|\n*Jun-yeol and Je-hoon loaned 2 bicycles and ride around Playa Gir\u00f3n.\n*They were not able to rent a car for next day (Day 11) to Trinidad as there was no cars available, instead they booked a 10:30 am bus ride.\n|-\n!rowspan=3|7\n|rowspan=3|4 April 2019\n|rowspan=2|11\n|rowspan=2|{{small|5 January 2019}}\n|\n*Jun-yeol and Je-hoon managed to arrive on time at the bus station to get on the bus to Trinidad.\n|-\n|rowspan=5 style=background:silver|[[Trinidad, Cuba|Trinidad]]\n|\n*After arriving at Trinidad in the afternoon, they spend some time to get accommodation for 4 nights and 3 days stay in Trinidad.\n*Jun-yeol explore part of Trinidad while Je-hoon stay at the casa.\n*After Jun-yeol return to the casa, Jun-yeol & Je-hoon left the casa for their dinner at the city.\n|-\n|rowspan=2|12\n|rowspan=2|{{small|6 January 2019}}\n|\n*After breakfast, they decide to go separate ways to explore different places in Trinidad.\n|-\n!rowspan=2|8\n|rowspan=2|11 April 2019\n|\n*They have a miscommunication of the meeting place at the Plaza but is still able to meet up.\n*After a late lunch, they end the day by visiting Playa Caribe beach to enjoy the sunset scene.\n|-\n|13\n|{{small|7 January 2019}}\n|\n*After breakfast, they took a train ride to visit '''The Manaca Iznaga Tower''' (the tallest lookout tower ever built in the Caribbean sugar region) at [[Valle de los Ingenios]].\n|-\n!rowspan=2|9\n|rowspan=2|18 April 2019\n|rowspan=2|14\n|rowspan=2|{{small|8 January 2019}}\n|\n*They left the casa very early in the morning to see the sunrise on a radio tower hill.\n*They managed to get a taxi to Varadero. The journey took 4 hours.\n|-\n|rowspan=2 style=background:pink|[[Varadero]]\n|\n*After the hotel check-in, they visit the beach to enjoy the scenic view of the beach.\n|-\n!rowspan=2|10\n|rowspan=2|25 April 2019\n|rowspan=2|15 \u2013 16\n|rowspan=2|{{small|9 \u2013 10 January 2019}}\n|\n*In the morning, they woke up early to walk at the beach before having their breakfast.\n*They managed to get a taxi reservation for the afternoon travel to Havana.\n|-\n|style=background:#7DF9FF|[[Havana]]\n|\n*They arrived at Havana in the late afternoon.\n*The production team showed a short clip of Jun-yeol visiting his aunt and her family in Mexico City during his layover from Seoul to Havana (26 December 2018).\n*Director's Cut & recap of the places visited and people they met.\n|-\n|}\n{{hidden end}}\n\n===Season 2 (2020)===\n{{hidden begin||expanded=1\n|title=List of episodes in Season 2\n|titlestyle=background:PaleTurquoise;\n}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+\n!width=\"30\" |{{abbr|Ep.|Episode}}\n!width=\"150\" |Broadcast date\n!width=\"60\" |Day\n!Filming date\n!Location\n!Notes\n|-\n!1\n|15 February 2020\n|1\n|{{small|30 November 2019}}\n|rowspan=3 style=background:PaleGreen|[[Buenos Aires]]\n|\"They Don't Know Soccer, But Argentina Anyway\"\n*Jae-hong, Ha-neul & Seong-wu arrived at the Buenos Aires Airport after 31 hours of flight and were surprised that idol fans were at the airport to catch a glimpse of Seong-wu.\n*After arriving at the accommodation, they visited the city centre to exchange currency and get SIM cards.\n*They visited the [[Obelisco de Buenos Aires|Obelisk]] and [[La Boca]].\n|-\n!2\n|22 February 2020\n|2\n|{{small|1 December 2019}}\n|\"Skydiving Surprise\"\n*Jae-hong, Ha-neul & Seong-wu had decided to do individual travel for first half of the day.\n**Seong-wu visited [[9 de Julio Avenue|July 9 Avenue]] and did tai-chi in the park.\n**Jae-hong visited a cafe recommended on Google for brunch.\n**Ha-neul had brunch and studying the script for a new theatre play.\n*On the Sunday afternoon, they visited [[San Telmo, Buenos Aires|San Telmo]] market which stretch out {{convert|1.3|km|mi|abbr=on}} between [[Plaza de Mayo]] and [[Plaza Dorrego]].\n**They walked and bought some souvenirs\n**After the market tour, they made a reservation of the [[skydiving]] for the following day.\n*They had their dinner in a famous steakhouse and spent the rest of the evening listening to live music and watch tango dance performances in an old tango bar.\n|-\n!rowspan=3|3\n|rowspan=3|29 February 2020\n|3\n|{{small|2 December 2019}}\n|\"When the Parachute Opens\"\n*They took a transport, provided by the skydiving company, to the airfield for their skydiving experience.\n*Jae-hong and one of the production staff are the first to do the skydiving while Ha-neul & Seong-wu will skydive on the second flight. Both group will dive from {{convert|3000|m|ft|abbr=on}} above ground.\n|-\n|4\n|{{small|3 December 2019}}\n|rowspan=3 style=background:#7DF9FF|[[Puerto Iguazu]]\n|\n*They took a two hours flight to Puerto Iguazu and spent a night in the hotel.\n|-\n|rowspan=2|5\n|rowspan=2|{{small|4 December 2019}}\n|rowspan=2|\"Throat on a Rainy Day\"\n*Their plan is to visit [[Iguazu Falls]], one of the three great waterfalls in the world, located at [[Iguaz\u00fa National Park]].\n**They start the visit by walking on the Green Trail \u2192 Lower Trail towards the Devil's Throat waterfall.\n**The next waterfall is Salto San Martin, second in size after Devil's Throat. They were amazed by the view of the waterfall upclose.\n**They took a train ride to Devil's Throat waterfall as they have a boat tour reservation.\n*After the Iguazu Falls tour, they return to the hotel and had dinner at a restaurant.\n|-\n!rowspan=2|4\n|rowspan=2|7 March 2020\n|-\n|rowspan=2|6\n|rowspan=2|{{small|5 December 2019}}\n|rowspan=3 style=background:lightgray|[[El Calafate]]\n|rowspan=2|\"Unexpected Room\"\n*They took a flight to Cordoba, then to El Calafate.\n*After arriving at their accommodation and will be their home for the next five days. They made enquires on bicycle rental from the staff of the service apartment.\n*They ride their bicycles around the neighbourhood and [[Argentino Lake|Lago Argentino]] to enjoy the windy weather.\n*After returning their bicycles, they move their belongings to their room. They were surprised that there was an additional room (with 2 beds) at the basement.\n*They decided to dine out for dinner due to the travelling schedule. They enjoyed their meal and the view of the sunset from the restaurant.\n|-\n!5\n|14 March 2020\n|-\n!6\n|21 March 2020\n|7\n|{{small|6 December 2019}}\n|\"Everything About the Glacier Is Mysterious\"\n*Ha-neul is the only traveller who decided to have breakfast at their accommodation while Jae-hong and Seong-wu skipped.\n*After breakfast, they visited [[Perito Moreno Glacier]], located in the [[Los Glaciares National Park]]. They are accompanied by a local guide.\n*Before reach their destination, the bus stopped at Argentino Lake and Andes for the travellers to take pictures.\n*The bus also stopped at Mirador de los Suspiros (Balcony of Sighs) for the view of the glaciers at a dsitance. The strong wind cause the camera of the prouduction team to shake a lot.\n*After reaching the Los Glaciares National Park, they headed to the observatories to see the Perito Moreno Glacier up close.\n*The glacier has an average height of {{convert|74|m|ft|abbr=on}}, width of {{convert|5|km|mi|abbr=on}} and length of {{convert|30|km|mi|abbr=on}}. The area of glacier (250&nbsp;km{{sup|2}}) is bigger than the size of Buenos Aires (203&nbsp;km{{sup|2}}).\n*They are overwhelmed by the enormous size of the glacier.\n*They notice the different in gray colour of the water on the left of glacier as it is due to the lime in the water while the right side is blue.\n*The local guide explain that they might be lucky to witness the collapse (or rupture) of the ice tunnel, that happens every 2 or 3 years, on the glacier as many broadcasting companies will come to make documentories and television programs.\n*They decided to eat some gimbap while wait for the glacier to [[Ice calving|calve]] (fall). They were able to witness the calving of the glacier after over an hour of waiting.\n*As it approach midday, more calving of the glacier are captured by the production team.\n*After lunch, they took a boat from the dock and reach the edge of the glacier for a mini-trekking experience. The trekking guide explained how the water holes (moulin) on the glacier is formed.\n*After trekking, they visited the supermarket to buy groceries to cook jjapaguri for their dinner. They were surprised on how cheap the price of ribeye and tenderloin are as compared to South Korea.\n|-\n!7\n|28 March 2020\n|8\n|{{small|7 December 2019}}\n|style=background:lightpink|[[Fitz Roy]]\n|\"Class of Fitz Roy\"\n|-\n|}\n{{hidden end}}\n\n==Original soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name      = Traveler \u2013 Argentina Original Television Soundtrack\n| type      = [[soundtrack]]\n| artist    = Various Artists\n| released  = 2020\n| genre     = [[Soundtrack]]\n| language  = {{hlist|[[Korean language|Korean]]|[[English language|English]]}}\n| label     = [[Kakao M]]\n}}\n{{-}}\n\n===Part 1===\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Released on {{start date|2020|2|16|df=y}}\n| extra_column = Artist\n| title1 = Traveler's Song\n| note1 = \ub5a0\ub098\uc9c0 \ubabb\ud560 \uc774\uc720\ub294 \uc5c6\uc5c8\ub2e4\ub294 \uac78\n| lyrics1 = Harim\n| music1 = Harim\n| extra1 = Harim\n| length1 = 4:06\n| title2 = Traveler's Song\n| note2 = Guitar Ver.\n| lyrics2 = Harim\n| music2 = Harim\n| extra2 = Harim\n| length2 = 4:46\n| title3 = Traveler's Song\n| note3 = Inst.\n| music3 = Harim\n| length3 = 4:06\n| title4 = Traveler's Song\n| note4 = Guitar Ver.) (Inst.\n| music4 = Harim\n| length4 = 4:46\n| total_length = 17:44\n}}\n\n===Part 2===\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Released on {{start date|2020|2|22|df=y}}\n| extra_column = Artist\n| title1 = Sometimes (Prod. [[Rocoberry]])\n| note1 = \uac00\ub054\uc740 \uadf8\ub798\ub3c4 \uad1c\ucc2e\uc544\n| lyrics1 = {{hlist|Conan|Roco}}\n| music1 = Conan\n| extra1 = O.WHEN\n| length1 = 3:14\n| title2 = Sometimes (Prod. Rocoberry)\n| note2 = Inst.\n| music2 = Conan\n| length2 = 3:14\n| total_length = 6:28\n}}\n\n===Part 3===\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Released on {{start date|2020|2|29|df=y}}\n| extra_column = Artist\n| title1 = Before Sunrise (Prod. [[Kiggen]])\n| lyrics1 = Kim Cho-yeon\n| music1 = {{hlist|Kiggen|Sean Michael Alexander|Drew Ryan Scott}}\n| extra1 = [[Soyou]]\n| length1 = 3:40\n| title2 = Before Sunrise (Prod. Kiggen)\n| note2 = Inst.\n| music2 = {{hlist|Kiggen|Sean Michael Alexander|Drew Ryan Scott}}\n| length2 = 3:40\n| total_length = 7:20\n}}\n\n===Part 4===\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Released on {{start date|2020|3|14|df=y}}\n| extra_column = Artist\n| title1 = Flower (Prod. [[Rocoberry]])\n| note1 = \uaf43\uc740 \ub530\ub77c\uc11c\n| lyrics1 = {{hlist|Conan|Roco}}\n| music1 = Conan\n| extra1 = Rothy\n| length1 = 3:54\n| title2 = Flower (Prod. Rocoberry)\n| note2 = Inst.\n| music2 = Conan\n| length2 = 3:54\n| total_length = 7:48\n}}\n\n===Part 5===\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Released on {{start date|2020|3|29|df=y}}\n| extra_column = Artist\n| title1 = Wish\n| note1 = \ubc14\ub78c\n| lyrics1 = Jukjae\n| music1 = Jukjae\n| extra1 = Jukjae\n| length1 = 4:34\n| title2 = Wish\n| note2 = Inst.\n| music2 = Jukjae\n| length2 = 4:34\n| total_length = 9:08\n}}\n\n==Ratings==\nIn these tables, {{color|blue|'''the blue numbers'''}} represent the lowest ratings and {{color|red|'''the red numbers'''}} represent the highest ratings.\n\n{{col-begin|width=auto}}\n{{col-break}}\n===Season 1===\n{|class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n!colspan=2|2019\n!rowspan=2 width=110|AGB Nielsen<br><ref name=nielsen1>{{citeweb|url=https://search.naver.com/search.