{"title_page": "Thomas & Friends (series 2)", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=April 2008}}\n{{Infobox television season\n  | season_number = 2\n  | bgcolour = #1F5C8F\n  | image = Thomas and Friends DVD Cover - Series 2.jpg\n  | image_upright = 1.15\n  | caption = DVD cover art\n  | country = [[United Kingdom]]\n  | network = [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]\n  | first_aired = {{Start date|1998|09|24|df=y}}\n  | last_aired = {{Start date|2000|12|17|df=y}}\n  | num_episodes = 13\n  | episode_list = List of Thomas & Friends episodes\n}}\n'''''[[Thomas & Friends|Thomas the Tank Engine & Friends]]''''' is a [[children's television series]] about the [[engines]] and other characters working on the railways of the [[Island of Sodor]], and is based on [[The Railway Series]] books written by the [[Wilbert Awdry|Rev. W. Awdry]].\n\nThis article lists and details episodes from the second series of the show, which was first broadcast in 1986.<ref name=\"TVARK\">{{cite web| url=http://www2.tv-ark.org.uk/itvlondon/thames-cont1.html | title=TVARK ITV London Thames Television | accessdate=10 November 2014 | publisher = TVARK}}</ref> This series was initially narrated by [[Ringo Starr]] for the U.K. audiences, who re-narrated 17 episodes for the U.S. audiences on ''[[Shining Time Station]]'' in 1991. The entire series was later re-narrated by [[George Carlin]] for the U.S. audiences.\n\nIt was produced by Clearwater Features Ltd. for [[Britt Allcroft]] (Thomas) Ltd.\n\n==Production==\n===Stories===\n[[Christopher Awdry]] was commissioned to write a new ''Railway Series'' book as source material for the second series. Three stories from ''[[List of Railway Series books#More About Thomas the Tank Engine|More About Thomas the Tank Engine]]'' provided additional roles for [[Bertie the Bus]], [[Terence the Tractor]], and [[Harold the Helicopter]]. The episodes \"Thomas and the Missing Christmas Tree\" and \"Thomas and Trevor\" were both one-off stories written by Christopher. The following series would begin to use original stories by the production staff, with some of the remaining ''Railway Series'' stories deemed \"repetitive and too 'story-book' orientated\".<ref name=intsa>http://www.sodor-island.net/steveasquithinterview.html</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nEarly in production, a third episode based on ''[[List of Railway Series books#The Twin Engines|The Twin Engines]]'' was due to be filmed, based largely on the story \"[[List of Railway Series books#The Twin Engines|The Missing Coach]]\". The model crew had gone as far as filming scenes on the Tidmouth Station set with Thomas arriving at the station, before [[Britt Allcroft]] decided the episode had too little action and its storyline would be too difficult to understand by younger viewers.<ref name=mittoninterview>http://www.sodor-island.net/interviews.html</ref> Subsequently, the episode was cancelled and replaced with Thomas, Percy and the Coal. Several promotional stills from the filming of The Missing Coach have surfaced in various ''Thomas'' publications, while David Mitton was believed to be in possession of the original film footage.\n\n==Episodes==\n<onlyinclude>{{Episode table\n|background=#1F5C8F|overall=|season=|title=|titleT=UK title (top)<hr />US title (bottom)|director=|aux2=|aux2T=Source|airdate=|episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=27\n |EpisodeNumber2=1\n |Title=Thomas, Percy & the Coal\"<hr />\"Double Trouble\n |DirectedBy= [[David Mitton]]\n |Aux2=''[[List of Railway Series books#More About Thomas the Tank Engine|More About Thomas the Tank Engine]]''<br />by [[Christopher Awdry]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|09|24|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas brags to Percy and Toby about how \"blue is the only proper colour for a really useful engine\". Later, he gets trapped under a coal hopper, which ruins his paintwork. He blames an amused Percy for his incident (because Percy inadvertently moved the careless trucks out from under the hopper), until Percy has his own trouble with coal.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=28\n |EpisodeNumber2=2\n |Title=Cows\"<hr />\"A Cow on the Line\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''[[List of Railway Series books#Edward the Blue Engine|Edward the Blue Engine]]''<br />by [[Wilbert Awdry|Rev. W. Awdry]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|09|24|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Gordon and Henry tease Edward after some cows break part of his train away. Edward has the last laugh however, when Gordon and Henry end up being stalled by a cow on the bridge.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=29\n |EpisodeNumber2=3\n |Title=Bertie's Chase\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Edward the Blue Engine''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|01|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas' fireman is unable to come in to work one day and Bertie agrees to take his passengers. Unaware of the change of plan, Edward leaves before Bertie arrives and so Bertie has to chase after him.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=30\n |EpisodeNumber2=4\n |Title=Saved From Scrap\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Edward the Blue Engine''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|01|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=At the scrapyard, Edward meets a traction engine called Trevor, who is due to be broken up, despite being in good condition. Edward is determined to save him and finds the man to do so.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=31\n |EpisodeNumber2=5\n |Title=Old Iron\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Edward the Blue Engine''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|08|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=James calls Edward slow, but when two boys meddle with James' controls and he speeds down the line, Edward chases down James to rescue him.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=32\n |EpisodeNumber2=6\n |Title=Thomas & Trevor\"<hr />\"A New Friend for Thomas\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=[[Thomas & Friends annuals#1988 Annual|1988 ''Thomas Annual'']]<br />story by Christopher Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|08|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Trevor is bored of working in the vicarage orchard, so Edward takes him to meet and help Thomas at the new harbor. Slowly but surely, a skeptical Thomas gains a respect for Trevor the traction engine.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=33\n |EpisodeNumber2=7\n |Title=Percy & the Signal\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''[[List of Railway Series books#Percy the Small Engine|Percy the Small Engine]]''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|15|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Percy is playing tricks on the bigger engines, first annoying Gordon and then tricking James to stay in his shed all day. But James and Gordon get revenge by tricking Percy into misreading a signal that goes up, referring to it as a \"backing signal\".\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=34\n |EpisodeNumber2=8\n |Title=Duck Takes Charge\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Percy the Small Engine''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|15|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=The Fat Controller buys an engine named Montague (nicknamed \"Duck\") to help out an overworked Percy. The big engines start ordering him about, so Duck and Percy decide to take matters into their own wheels.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=35\n |EpisodeNumber2=9\n |Title=Percy & Harold\"<hr />\"Percy Proves a Point\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Percy the Small Engine''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|22|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Percy is sent to work at the new harbor and challenges a helicopter called Harold to a race to the wharf.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=36\n |EpisodeNumber2=10\n |Title=The Runaway\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''More About Thomas the Tank Engine''<br />by Christopher Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|22|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas isn't feeling well and has to go to the works. He soon comes back, but with a problem in his brakes. This proves disastrous when a temporary fireman forgets to tighten them properly and Thomas puffs away uncontrollably.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=37\n |EpisodeNumber2=11\n |Title=Percy Takes the Plunge\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''[[List of Railway Series books#The Eight Famous Engines|The Eight Famous Engines]]''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|29|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Percy boasts that \"water is nothing to an engine with determination\", which annoys Henry, but curiosity gets the better of him when he wants to see why he is forbidden to pass the \"Danger\" board on the quay. Percy asks the trucks for help, but soon wishes he hadn't, when the trucks push him into the sea.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=38\n |EpisodeNumber2=12\n |Title=Pop Goes the Diesel\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''[[List of Railway Series books#Duck and the Diesel Engine|Duck and the Diesel Engine]]''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|29|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=A diesel engine, named Diesel, arrives on the island and Duck is given the task of showing him what to do. Diesel boasts that his kind are \"revolutionary\" and they know everything, so Duck leaves him to shunt some old trucks alone, with disastrous results.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n 