86|11|12|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Donald and Douglas are twin engines whom The Fat Controller had bought from Scotland to help out, although only one engine had been expected. He intends to send one of them back and a spiteful brake van only makes things worse.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=43\n |EpisodeNumber2=17\n |Title=The Deputation\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''The Twin Engines''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|11|19|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Heavy snow has fallen on Sodor, but Donald and Douglas are used to it, using their snowploughs to clear the line. After they help Henry from a snowdrift, the other engines are determined to help both of them stay on Sodor, as the returning home one will be turned into scrap.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=44\n |EpisodeNumber2=18\n |Title=Thomas Comes to Breakfast\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''[[List of Railway Series books#Branch Line Engines|Branch Line Engines]]''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|11|19|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas' driver jokingly tells him that he could almost manage running the branch line on his own. Thomas thinks he's being honest, but when he tries to move by himself, he ends up crashing straight into the stationmaster's house.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=45\n |EpisodeNumber2=19\n |Title=Daisy\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Branch Line Engines''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|11|26|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Daisy, a diesel railcar, has been bought to help Percy and Toby while Thomas is being mended. However, she proves to be very stubborn and later she causes trouble at the station when refusing to pull a milk tanker.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=46\n |EpisodeNumber2=20\n |Title=Percy's Predicament\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Branch Line Engines''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|11|26|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Toby offers to swap jobs with Percy, while he takes the milk Daisy keeps leaving behind. Unfortunately, Percy has never worked at the quarry before, and he begins to delight in ordering the trucks about until the trucks get fed up with this and decide to retaliate, by pushing him down the line and into the back of a goods train. Daisy is told off by The Fat Controller for being lazy and promises to change her ways with help from Toby. Thomas soon returns and Percy is sent to be mended.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=47\n |EpisodeNumber2=21\n |Title=The Diseasel\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''[[List of Railway Series books#Main Line Engines|Main Line Engines]]''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|12|03|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Bill and Ben are tank engine twins who work at the China Clay Pits. One day, they are aghast when they discover that their China Clay Trucks have gone missing. They mistakenly believe that their trucks were \"magicked away\" by a \"diseasel\" and go on a search to find them.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=48\n |EpisodeNumber2=22\n |Title=Wrong Road\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Main Line Engines''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|12|03|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Gordon remarks that branch lines are vulgar and that The Fat Controller would never approve of him running on one. However, due to a case of mistaken identity involving a lady's hat, Gordon ends up on the branch line, where Bill and Ben are waiting.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=49\n |EpisodeNumber2=23\n |Title= Edward's Exploit\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Main Line Engines''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|12|10|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Some tourists are visiting the Island of Sodor and Edward is due to take them to meet Bill and Ben. On the journey back, one of his crank pins, which hold his side rods on, breaks off. Despite this, Edward presses on and gets the tourists back safely.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=50\n |EpisodeNumber2=24\n |Title=Ghost Train\"<hr />\"Percy's Ghostly Trick\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''[[List of Railway Series books#Tramway Engines|Tramway Engines]]''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|12|10|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas doesn't believe Percy when he tells him about a ghost train his driver saw the previous night (which turns out to be a television one). That night, Percy crashes into a cart of lime powder, turning him pale white and decides to play a ghostly trick on Thomas. \n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=51\n |EpisodeNumber2=25\n |Title=Woolly Bear\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Tramway Engines''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|12|17|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Percy is still teasing Thomas about the ghost incident. Thomas retorts by calling Percy a green caterpillar with red stripes and chews him out for being late. Soon afterwards, Percy decides to start home from the harbor early, but gets hit by a crate of [[treacle]]. When he leaves still sticky, he then gets stuck on a hill, windswept with hay. Percy arrives back at the station covered in hay, to Thomas' amusement.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=52\n |EpisodeNumber2=26\n |Title=Thomas & the Missing Christmas Tree\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=[[List of Railway Series books#Thomas and the Missing Christmas Tree|''Thomas and the Missing Christmas Tree'']]<br />by Christopher Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|12|17|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=It's the day before Christmas Eve and all the engines are at work getting ready for the Christmas Party. Thomas is sent to collect the Christmas tree, but he gets buried in a huge snowdrift on the way back. Donald and Douglas come to the rescue and bring him back in time for the party.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n}} </onlyinclude>\n\n==Characters==\n\n===Introduced===\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[Bluebell the Cow]] (\"Cows\")\n* [[Trevor the Traction Engine]] (\"Saved from Scrap\")\n* [[The Vicar (Thomas & Friends)|The Vicar of Wellsworth]] (\"Saved from Scrap\")\n* [[Jem Cole]] (\"Saved from Scrap\")\n* [[Duck the Great Western Engine]] (\"Duck Takes Charge\")\n* [[Harold the Helicopter]] (\"Percy & Harold\")\n* [[Diesel (Thomas & Friends)|Devious Diesel]] (\"Pop Goes the Diesel\")\n* [[Donald and Douglas|Donald and Douglas the Scottish Twins]] (\"Break Van\")\n* [[Rolling stock (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#The Spiteful Brakevan|The Spiteful Brakevan]] (\"Break Van\")\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Daisy|Daisy the Diesel Railcar]] (\"Daisy\")\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Bill and Ben|Bill and Ben the Tank Engine Twins]] (\"Percy Takes the Plunge\" {{small|(''not named yet'')}} / \"The Diseasel\")\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#BoCo|BoCo the Diesel Engine]] (\"The Diseasel\")\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Recurring cast===\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n*[[Thomas the Tank Engine|Thomas]]\n*[[Edward the Blue Engine|Edward]]\n*[[Henry the Green Engine|Henry]]\n*[[Gordon the Big Engine|Gordon]]\n*[[James the Red Engine|James]]\n*[[Percy the Small Engine|Percy]]\n*[[Toby the Tram Engine|Toby]]\n*[[Bertie the Bus|Bertie]]\n*[[Terence the Tractor|Terence]]\n*[[Rolling stock (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Henrietta|Henrietta]]\n*[[Annie and Clarabel]]\n*[[Rolling stock (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Troublesome Trucks|Troublesome Trucks]]\n*[[The Fat Controller|Sir Topham Hatt/The Fat Controller]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Thomas}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2011}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Thomas And Friends (Series 02)}}\n[[Category:Festival Records video albums]]\n[[Category:Mushroom Records video albums]]\n[[Category:Warner Records video albums]]\n[[Category:1986 British television seasons]]\n[[Category:Thomas & Friends seasons]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=April 2008}}\n{{Infobox television season\n  | season_number = 2\n  | bgcolour = #1F5C8F\n  | image = Thomas and Friends DVD Cover - Series 2.jpg\n  | image_upright = 1.15\n  | caption = DVD cover art\n  | country = [[United Kingdom]]\n  | network = [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]\n  | first_aired = {{Start date|1986|09|24|df=y}}\n  | last_aired = {{Start date|1986|12|17|df=y}}\n  | num_episodes = 26\n  | episode_list = List of Thomas & Friends episodes\n}}\n'''''[[Thomas & Friends|Thomas the Tank Engine & Friends]]''''' is a [[children's television series]] about the [[engines]] and other characters working on the railways of the [[Island of Sodor]], and is based on [[The Railway Series]] books written by the [[Wilbert Awdry|Rev. W. Awdry]].\n\nThis article lists and details episodes from the second series of the show, which was first broadcast in 1986.<ref name=\"TVARK\">{{cite web| url=http://www2.tv-ark.org.uk/itvlondon/thames-cont1.html | title=TVARK ITV London Thames Television | accessdate=10 November 2014 | publisher = TVARK}}</ref> This series was initially narrated by [[Ringo Starr]] for the U.K. audiences, who re-narrated 17 episodes for the U.S. audiences on ''[[Shining Time Station]]'' in 1991. The entire series was later re-narrated by [[George Carlin]] for the U.S. audiences.\n\nIt was produced by Clearwater Features Ltd. for [[Britt Allcroft]] (Thomas) Ltd.\n\n==Production==\n===Stories===\n[[Christopher Awdry]] was commissioned to write a new ''Railway Series'' book as source material for the second series. Three stories from ''[[List of Railway Series books#More About Thomas the Tank Engine|More About Thomas the Tank Engine]]'' provided additional roles for [[Bertie the Bus]], [[Terence the Tractor]], and [[Harold the Helicopter]]. The episodes \"Thomas and the Missing Christmas Tree\" and \"Thomas and Trevor\" were both one-off stories written by Christopher. The following series would begin to use original stories by the production staff, with some of the remaining ''Railway Series'' stories deemed \"repetitive and too 'story-book' orientated\".<ref name=intsa>http://www.sodor-island.net/steveasquithinterview.html</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nEarly in production, a third episode based on ''[[List of Railway Series books#The Twin Engines|The Twin Engines]]'' was due to be filmed, based largely on the story \"[[List of Railway Series books#The Twin Engines|The Missing Coach]]\". The model crew had gone as far as filming scenes on the Tidmouth Station set with Thomas arriving at the station, before [[Britt Allcroft]] decided the episode had too little action and its storyline would be too difficult to understand by younger viewers.<ref name=mittoninterview>http://www.sodor-island.net/interviews.html</ref> Subsequently, the episode was cancelled and replaced with Thomas, Percy and the Coal. Several promotional stills from the filming of The Missing Coach have surfaced in various ''Thomas'' publications, while David Mitton was believed to be in possession of the original film footage.\n\n==Episodes==\n<onlyinclude>{{Episode table\n|background=#1F5C8F|overall=|season=|title=|titleT=UK title (top)<hr />US title (bottom)|director=|aux2=|aux2T=Source|airdate=|episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=27\n |EpisodeNumber2=1\n |Title=Thomas, Percy & the Coal\"<hr />\"Double Trouble\n |DirectedBy= [[David Mitton]]\n |Aux2=''[[List of Railway Series books#More About Thomas the Tank Engine|More About Thomas the Tank Engine]]''<br />by [[Christopher Awdry]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|09|24|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas brags to Percy and Toby about how \"blue is the only proper colour for a really useful engine\". Later, he gets trapped under a coal hopper, which ruins his paintwork. He blames an amused Percy for his incident (because Percy inadvertently moved the careless trucks out from under the hopper), until Percy has his own trouble with coal.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=28\n |EpisodeNumber2=2\n |Title=Cows\"<hr />\"A Cow on the Line\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''[[List of Railway Series books#Edward the Blue Engine|Edward the Blue Engine]]''<br />by [[Wilbert Awdry|Rev. W. Awdry]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|09|24|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Gordon and Henry tease Edward after some cows break part of his train away. Edward has the last laugh however, when Gordon and Henry end up being stalled by a cow on the bridge.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=29\n |EpisodeNumber2=3\n |Title=Bertie's Chase\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Edward the Blue Engine''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|01|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas' fireman is unable to come in to work one day and Bertie agrees to take his passengers. Unaware of the change of plan, Edward leaves before Bertie arrives and so Bertie has to chase after him.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=30\n |EpisodeNumber2=4\n |Title=Saved From Scrap\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Edward the Blue Engine''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|01|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=At the scrapyard, Edward meets a traction engine called Trevor, who is due to be broken up, despite being in good condition. Edward is determined to save him and finds the man to do so.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=31\n |EpisodeNumber2=5\n |Title=Old Iron\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Edward the Blue Engine''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|08|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=James calls Edward slow, but when two boys meddle with James' controls and he speeds down the line, Edward chases down James to rescue him.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=32\n |EpisodeNumber2=6\n |Title=Thomas & Trevor\"<hr />\"A New Friend for Thomas\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=[[Thomas & Friends annuals#1988 Annual|1988 ''Thomas Annual'']]<br />story by Christopher Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|08|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Trevor is bored of working in the vicarage orchard, so Edward takes him to meet and help Thomas at the new harbor. Slowly but surely, a skeptical Thomas gains a respect for Trevor the traction engine.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=33\n |EpisodeNumber2=7\n |Title=Percy & the Signal\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''[[List of Railway Series books#Percy the Small Engine|Percy the Small Engine]]''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|15|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Percy is playing tricks on the bigger engines, first annoying Gordon and then tricking James to stay in his shed all day. But James and Gordon get revenge by tricking Percy into misreading a signal that goes up, referring to it as a \"backing signal\".\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=34\n |EpisodeNumber2=8\n |Title=Duck Takes Charge\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=''Percy the Small Engine''<br />by Rev. W. Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|10|15|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=The Fat Controller buys an engine named Montague (nicknamed \"Duck\") to help out an overworked P