cky, he then gets stuck on a hill, windswept with hay. Percy arrives back at the station covered in hay, to Thomas' amusement.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 2)\n |EpisodeNumber=52\n |EpisodeNumber2=26\n |Title=Thomas & the Missing Christmas Tree\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=[[List of Railway Series books#Thomas and the Missing Christmas Tree|''Thomas and the Missing Christmas Tree'']]<br />by Christopher Awdry\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1986|12|17|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=It's the day before Christmas Eve and all the engines are at work getting ready for the Christmas Party. Thomas is sent to collect the Christmas tree, but he gets buried in a huge snowdrift on the way back. Donald and Douglas come to the rescue and bring him back in time for the party.\n |LineColor=1F5C8F\n}}\n}} </onlyinclude>\n\n==Characters==\n\n===Introduced===\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[Bluebell the Cow]] (\"Cows\")\n* [[Trevor the Traction Engine]] (\"Saved from Scrap\")\n* [[The Vicar (Thomas & Friends)|The Vicar of Wellsworth]] (\"Saved from Scrap\")\n* [[Jem Cole]] (\"Saved from Scrap\")\n* [[Duck the Great Western Engine]] (\"Duck Takes Charge\")\n* [[Harold the Helicopter]] (\"Percy & Harold\")\n* [[Diesel (Thomas & Friends)|Devious Diesel]] (\"Pop Goes the Diesel\")\n* [[Donald and Douglas|Donald and Douglas the Scottish Twins]] (\"Break Van\")\n* [[Rolling stock (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#The Spiteful Brakevan|The Spiteful Brakevan]] (\"Break Van\")\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Daisy|Daisy the Diesel Railcar]] (\"Daisy\")\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Bill and Ben|Bill and Ben the Tank Engine Twins]] (\"Percy Takes the Plunge\" {{small|(''not named yet'')}} / \"The Diseasel\")\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#BoCo|BoCo the Diesel Engine]] (\"The Diseasel\")\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Recurring cast===\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n*[[Thomas the 